China , Philippines Agree to Strengthen Cooperation
KUALA LUMPUR , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- Foreign ministers of China and the Philippines Saturday exchanged views on bilateral relations and expressed their desire to strengthen the relations .
Both Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and his Philippine counterpart Domingol Siazon are here to attend the 10th ministerial meeting of Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation ( APEC ) which began here Saturday .
Tang Jiaxuan said at present , Sino-Philippine relations , in general , continue to develop well .
The Chinese government and the Chinese people treasure the friendly relations of good-neighborhood with the Philippine government and the Philippine people and will always work hard to develop cooperation in different areas with the Philippines .
Appreciating Tang 's views , Siazon said the Philippines attaches great importance to its relations with China and the Philippines is satisfied with the political , economic and trade as well as cultural relations between the two countries .
Siazon hoped the friendly cooperation would be further strengthened .
The two ministers also exchanged views on the situation in South China Sea and on other issues of common concern , a Chinese official told reporters after the meeting .
Both China and the Philippines expressed their readiness to work together to solve their problems and develop their friendly relations .
